WEBVTT

00:54.320 --> 00:54.880
Xing.

00:55.040 --> 00:56.440
Stop watching TV.

00:57.360 --> 00:59.240
Do your Chinese homework later.

00:59.920 --> 01:00.680
Got it.

01:01.280 --> 01:01.840
Let's go.

01:06.240 --> 01:07.160
Aunt,

01:07.400 --> 01:09.000
let me watch a little longer.

01:09.840 --> 01:12.000
I really will just watch a little longer.

01:12.000 --> 01:13.280
What's the use of talking? Let's go.

01:13.280 --> 01:13.920
Aunt.

01:13.920 --> 01:15.480
Sister, you're the best.

01:15.760 --> 01:17.360
Just like when you were a kid.

01:18.440 --> 01:20.760
This poem is a Han Yuefu folk song.

01:21.320 --> 01:23.280
'He' means 'how'.

01:23.720 --> 01:25.480
'Tiantian' means

01:25.480 --> 01:27.720
the lotus leaves are growing lushly.

01:28.039 --> 01:29.570
I know everything you said.

01:30.360 --> 01:33.220
But the teacher asked us to write a 100-word review,

01:33.240 --> 01:34.970
and I can't write a single word.

01:35.759 --> 01:37.000
Then let's imagine,

01:37.560 --> 01:40.000
what kind of person wrote this poem?

01:40.280 --> 01:42.479
'River South is ripe for lotus picking.'

01:42.479 --> 01:45.410
So the person picking lotuses is looking at the fish.

01:45.520 --> 01:46.800
The lotus pickers in Jiangnan

01:46.800 --> 01:48.680
refer to young men and women.

01:49.080 --> 01:50.479
And the lotus picking time

01:50.479 --> 01:51.759
is right in midsummer.

01:52.520 --> 01:55.440
It's exactly when young men and women work together

01:55.759 --> 01:57.840
and express their love for each other.

01:57.840 --> 01:59.600
You know, 'lian' in lotus

01:59.680 --> 02:01.520
sounds like 'lian' in pity or affection,

02:01.520 --> 02:02.780
so it symbolizes love.

02:03.240 --> 02:04.600
So when he saw the fish

02:04.600 --> 02:05.530
playing around,

02:06.080 --> 02:07.600
he thought of himself

02:07.600 --> 02:10.660
picking lotuses and laughing with the person he likes.

02:10.800 --> 02:11.530
Understand?

02:11.920 --> 02:13.520
So it's a love poem after all.

02:16.240 --> 02:17.040
That's easy.

02:17.440 --> 02:18.920
I know a lot about love.

02:19.079 --> 02:20.040
What do you know?

02:20.560 --> 02:22.840
Like what happened with you and that big brother.

02:22.840 --> 02:24.800
Don't talk nonsense. What big brother?

02:24.800 --> 02:25.600
He walks you home every day.

02:25.600 --> 02:27.130
You pick lotuses together.

02:28.440 --> 02:29.720
Who told you to talk nonsense?

02:29.720 --> 02:31.180
I'm not talking nonsense.

02:31.920 --> 02:34.380
Don't you look at him on your phone every day?

02:35.280 --> 02:35.800
Give it back.

02:35.800 --> 02:36.360
I won't.

02:36.880 --> 02:37.360
Give me back my phone.

02:37.360 --> 02:37.800
I won't.

02:37.800 --> 02:38.440
Give it back.

02:38.440 --> 02:39.079
I won't.

02:40.440 --> 02:40.800
I won't.

02:40.800 --> 02:41.720
Give it back.

02:41.800 --> 02:42.400
Give it back to me.

02:42.400 --> 02:42.860
I won't.

02:43.360 --> 02:43.890
Hurry up.

02:43.920 --> 02:45.240
Xiaocen, how old are you?

02:45.240 --> 02:46.640
Are you still messing around with Xiaoxing?

02:46.640 --> 02:48.000
Auntie, my sister went lotus picking.

02:48.000 --> 02:48.400
You...

02:48.840 --> 02:49.970
What lotus picking?

02:51.160 --> 02:52.600
Xing, what are you saying?

02:52.600 --> 02:55.860
Sister is teaching me to recite a poem about lotus picking.

02:59.600 --> 03:01.800
Xing, have you finished your homework?

03:02.000 --> 03:03.460
Let's go do your homework.

03:14.040 --> 03:14.840
Good morning.

03:15.800 --> 03:16.400
Morning.

03:28.240 --> 03:29.100
Let me help you.

03:29.240 --> 03:29.800
No need.

03:30.480 --> 03:31.079
It's fine.

04:08.200 --> 04:09.460
What's wrong with you?

04:10.200 --> 04:11.200
Nothing.

04:12.880 --> 04:13.520
Nothing?

04:14.640 --> 04:15.400
Why does it seem like the more I talk to you,

04:15.400 --> 04:16.600
the more you avoid me?

04:16.720 --> 04:17.839
I'm not.

04:18.640 --> 04:19.300
You're not?

04:19.519 --> 04:20.079
No.

04:20.519 --> 04:22.380
You're not avoiding me right now?

04:22.720 --> 04:23.560
No.

04:25.160 --> 04:25.720
I'm not.

04:25.720 --> 04:26.520
Good morning.

04:28.120 --> 04:29.120
Why are you two bending down so low?

04:29.120 --> 04:30.180
What are you doing?

04:31.480 --> 04:32.040
Nothing.

04:33.080 --> 04:34.200
You guys keep talking.

04:34.200 --> 04:35.330
I'm rooting for you.

04:39.520 --> 04:42.520
In 'Notes of Mo'e', written during the late Yuan and early Ming dynasties,

04:42.520 --> 04:43.780
there is such a record.

04:44.320 --> 04:47.680
Craftsmen mixed gluten with lime to make an adhesive

04:47.920 --> 04:50.600
to glue together broken ceramics.

04:50.920 --> 04:52.040
What was its flaw?

04:52.640 --> 04:55.400
It couldn't be soaked in water for long.

04:56.040 --> 04:58.400
This means it wasn't waterproof.

04:59.000 --> 04:59.960
Shortly after,

05:00.280 --> 05:02.640
the ceramic stapling technique appeared.

05:02.640 --> 05:03.600
This small bowl

05:03.640 --> 05:06.560
was repaired using the ceramic stapling technique.

05:06.560 --> 05:07.960
Without a diamond drill,

05:08.000 --> 05:09.520
don't take up porcelain mending.

05:09.520 --> 05:11.250
This refers to this very craft.

05:11.440 --> 05:12.100
After that,

05:12.360 --> 05:15.220
the kintsugi craft, which focuses more on artistry

05:15.280 --> 05:19.080
and the aesthetic beauty of the artifacts, emerged.

05:19.840 --> 05:20.800
To be exact,

05:21.080 --> 05:22.140
the kintsugi craft

05:22.240 --> 05:24.640
should actually be called lacquer mending.

05:24.640 --> 05:28.170
It involves applying raw lacquer onto broken porcelain pieces

05:28.840 --> 05:30.480
and then gluing them together.

05:30.480 --> 05:31.680
Then, to the surface of the object,

05:31.680 --> 05:34.640
gold powder or gold leaf is applied

05:35.560 --> 05:37.090
to create this appearance.

05:39.520 --> 05:40.320
What's wrong?

05:41.880 --> 05:44.610
Xu Xiao asked me to go to Taoxichuan this weekend.

05:48.159 --> 05:49.360
Don't overthink it.

05:50.240 --> 05:51.200
He usually looks for me

05:51.200 --> 05:52.930
to talk about serious matters.

05:53.159 --> 05:55.420
What improper things are you expecting?

05:57.440 --> 05:59.040
Then go with me this weekend.

05:59.280 --> 05:59.800
Sorry.

06:00.160 --> 06:01.640
I have plans this weekend.

06:25.240 --> 06:26.900
Would it seem too deliberate?

06:43.640 --> 06:44.200
Xiaocen.

06:45.400 --> 06:45.960
Xu Xiao.

06:48.080 --> 06:50.080
Why did you ask me out to Taoxichuan?

06:51.240 --> 06:52.240
Didn't I tell you?

06:53.360 --> 06:55.360
There's a Youth Creative Fair here this weekend.

06:55.360 --> 06:57.280
Many young artists set up stalls here,

06:57.280 --> 06:59.409
so I wanted to invite you to take a look.

07:01.120 --> 07:01.600
I see.

07:01.760 --> 07:02.120
Yeah.

07:03.200 --> 07:04.460
Isn't it interesting?

07:07.560 --> 07:08.360
Let's go then.

07:08.360 --> 07:08.800
Okay.

07:11.680 --> 07:13.040
Come and take a look.

07:13.040 --> 07:14.160
Imitation Ru ware.

07:14.160 --> 07:17.000
One of the five great kilns of the Southern Song Dynasty.

07:17.000 --> 07:18.480
Come take a look.

07:18.480 --> 07:20.000
Our main products are flower cups.

07:20.000 --> 07:21.480
They are all underglaze colored.

07:21.480 --> 07:23.320
Safe, hygienic, and durable.

07:23.320 --> 07:23.980
Take a look.

07:28.240 --> 07:29.440
How much is this, sir?

07:30.680 --> 07:31.920
Does it have a theme?

07:32.040 --> 07:33.900
The theme of this porcelain shard

07:33.920 --> 07:35.640
is rebirth and repair.

07:37.520 --> 07:38.960
How much is this?

07:39.640 --> 07:40.840
Two hundred and eighty.

07:40.840 --> 07:42.170
Two hundred and eighty?

07:42.880 --> 07:45.340
These are artworks of ceramic restoration.

07:47.040 --> 07:48.170
These works of yours

07:48.720 --> 07:49.980
are not restorations.

07:50.240 --> 07:51.080
Your works

07:51.080 --> 07:53.360
are just joining broken porcelain pieces together.

07:53.360 --> 07:56.690
They should be considered cultural and creative products.

08:00.480 --> 08:02.210
Kid, are you buying something?

08:02.280 --> 08:03.410
Sorry to bother you.

08:06.040 --> 08:07.040
Stop right there.

08:07.840 --> 08:08.640
What's wrong?

08:08.800 --> 08:09.480
Come here.

08:11.480 --> 08:12.480
Look at our works.

08:12.960 --> 08:15.120
Was our work pieced together?

08:15.760 --> 08:17.560
Has it been brought back to life?

08:17.640 --> 08:19.600
How is that not considered restoration?

08:19.600 --> 08:20.330
First of all,

08:20.480 --> 08:22.640
restoration is a very rigorous process.

08:22.640 --> 08:23.840
On these works of yours,

08:23.840 --> 08:25.480
there is still residual glue.

08:25.480 --> 08:26.010
Besides,

08:26.680 --> 08:28.680
these are all imitation antique porcelain shards.

08:28.680 --> 08:29.680
You were scammed.

08:29.760 --> 08:32.020
Have you seen ancient porcelain shards?

08:32.240 --> 08:32.799
Jing.

08:32.960 --> 08:33.960
Jing. Jing. Jing.

08:34.159 --> 08:34.640
Sorry.

08:34.919 --> 08:36.000
That's just her temper.

08:36.000 --> 08:37.000
She meant no harm.

08:42.080 --> 08:42.600
Fine.

08:42.919 --> 08:44.720
Everyone has the right to speak.

08:44.760 --> 08:45.560
I'm sorry too.

08:45.920 --> 08:48.250
I was a bit reckless with my words just now.

08:50.840 --> 08:51.480
Let's go.

08:55.440 --> 08:56.040
I'm so mad.

08:56.040 --> 08:57.840
It's okay. It's okay. It's okay.

08:59.120 --> 08:59.640
Class.

09:00.160 --> 09:02.480
To master the ceramic stapling technique,

09:02.480 --> 09:05.280
we first need to learn how to make ceramic staples.

09:06.000 --> 09:06.680
Today,

09:06.960 --> 09:09.820
we will learn the method of making ceramic staples.

09:09.960 --> 09:11.520
The function of ceramic staples

09:11.520 --> 09:13.250
is to bind the broken porcelain

09:13.520 --> 09:15.080
tightly together.

09:16.040 --> 09:17.000
As for ceramic staples,

09:17.000 --> 09:19.360
there are traditional spindle-shaped staples

09:19.360 --> 09:22.090
as well as various styles of decorative staples.

09:22.440 --> 09:25.720
Ceramic stapling is using ceramic staples to bind broken objects

09:25.720 --> 09:27.240
tightly together.

09:27.840 --> 09:30.480
We call it binding objects with iron.

09:31.040 --> 09:34.280
It binds the broken porcelain tightly together.

09:34.680 --> 09:37.800
This is making the broken whole again.

10:21.040 --> 10:22.960
It's already mealtime,

10:23.320 --> 10:25.560
but no one from our class is in the cafeteria.

10:25.560 --> 10:26.490
What's going on?

10:26.760 --> 10:28.490
Is Mr. Yue's homework too hard?

10:28.720 --> 10:29.080
Yeah.

10:29.080 --> 10:30.340
Don't even mention it.

10:30.360 --> 10:31.880
He has us hammering ceramic staples.

10:31.880 --> 10:33.400
My hands are all blistered.

10:33.400 --> 10:35.360
We have no appetite, Mr. Liang.

10:35.520 --> 10:37.240
But it's mealtime. You still need to eat.

10:37.240 --> 10:38.320
I ruined a bunch of them.

10:38.320 --> 10:39.650
Now I have to start over.

10:39.720 --> 10:40.850
Then let me help you.

10:43.840 --> 10:44.680
Mr. Liang.

10:48.240 --> 10:50.500
Xu Xiao made this ceramic staple, right?

10:51.160 --> 10:52.760
Mr. Liang, how did you tell?

10:53.320 --> 10:54.440
With this kind of technique,

10:54.440 --> 10:56.400
you can tell at a glance it isn't newly learned.

10:56.400 --> 10:58.600
I heard Xu Xiao works at an antique shop.

10:58.920 --> 11:01.650
He must see ceramic stapling and kintsugi often.

11:01.960 --> 11:03.920
He finished his apprenticeship long ago.

11:03.920 --> 11:04.600
So,

11:05.480 --> 11:07.720
for the assignment Mr. Yue gave this time,

11:07.720 --> 11:09.000
in such a short time,

11:09.320 --> 11:10.920
only Xu Xiao could finish it.

11:14.760 --> 11:15.400
Look.

11:15.560 --> 11:16.920
No wonder he looked so familiar.

11:16.920 --> 11:18.320
He's the boy from before.

11:19.720 --> 11:21.320
The one who broke the antique

11:21.520 --> 11:23.920
and then cleared up the misunderstanding.

11:24.600 --> 11:25.930
He's quite popular now.

11:26.120 --> 11:27.400
He's got some fame.

11:30.880 --> 11:32.010
I'll get going then.

11:32.400 --> 11:32.800
Okay.

11:33.600 --> 11:34.660
Once I finish this,

11:34.680 --> 11:35.740
I'll head back too.

11:37.280 --> 11:38.000
Be careful on the road.

11:38.000 --> 11:39.080
Okay, bye.

11:39.600 --> 11:40.000
Bye.

11:49.800 --> 11:52.060
You are the girl from the market that day.

11:53.400 --> 11:54.200
Zhao Xiaocen.

11:55.520 --> 11:55.960
Hello.

11:58.160 --> 11:59.960
Did you make all these cups?

12:01.280 --> 12:02.340
I didn't make them.

12:02.640 --> 12:03.800
I just wrote on them.

12:04.600 --> 12:05.880
That's still impressive.

12:05.880 --> 12:07.140
They look really nice.

12:07.280 --> 12:07.880
Thank you.

12:09.280 --> 12:11.010
By the way, I'm here for Xu Xiao.

12:11.240 --> 12:11.840
Is he here?

12:12.880 --> 12:13.680
He's inside.

12:14.320 --> 12:14.920
Thank you.

12:34.640 --> 12:35.500
Hello, Xu Xiao.

12:39.040 --> 12:41.160
You are the one from Taoxichuan.

12:42.760 --> 12:44.160
What's up? Can I help you?

12:46.800 --> 12:47.930
I heard from a friend

12:47.960 --> 12:49.320
that you appraise treasures here.

12:49.320 --> 12:51.850
I have something I'd like you to take a look at.

12:52.160 --> 12:52.560
Sure.

12:53.320 --> 12:54.380
Please have a seat.

13:00.360 --> 13:01.000
This is it.

13:28.480 --> 13:29.410
Why are you back?

13:32.240 --> 13:33.640
I left something behind.

13:35.400 --> 13:35.800
It's

13:37.960 --> 13:39.090
over at Boss Wang's.

13:43.760 --> 13:44.880
Do you know where

13:44.880 --> 13:46.880
these porcelain pieces were found?

13:46.920 --> 13:48.850
Xianghu Village, Fuliang County.

13:49.000 --> 13:50.000
That explains it.

13:50.320 --> 13:51.840
The works I saw at your stall

13:51.840 --> 13:52.900
a couple of days ago

13:53.160 --> 13:55.290
were probably made by the same person.

13:56.600 --> 13:57.480
I found it!

13:58.320 --> 13:58.840
Okay.

14:02.280 --> 14:02.880
Be careful on the road.

14:02.880 --> 14:03.200
Bye.

14:03.200 --> 14:04.000
Bye, Xiaocen.

14:05.920 --> 14:07.120
You can tell all that?

14:15.280 --> 14:16.440
These broken porcelain pieces

14:16.440 --> 14:17.520
were obviously picked up from

14:17.520 --> 14:19.600
the ceramics dump in Xianghu Village.

14:19.600 --> 14:21.730
They are fragments of flawed pottery.

14:22.440 --> 14:24.120
Glued together with adhesive,

14:24.120 --> 14:25.640
it looks like turning waste into treasure

14:25.640 --> 14:26.840
and highly valuable,

14:27.880 --> 14:31.080
but there's actually not much technical skill involved.

14:32.120 --> 14:32.800
This item

14:33.640 --> 14:34.770
is fine to play with.

14:35.920 --> 14:36.720
In my opinion,

14:37.840 --> 14:39.370
it's not worth collecting.

14:45.440 --> 14:47.240
Then do you think a work like this

14:47.920 --> 14:49.000
can still be saved?

14:51.560 --> 14:53.160
From what I can see right now,

14:54.080 --> 14:55.840
it's about combining some

14:55.840 --> 14:58.040
more complex ceramics restoration techniques

14:58.040 --> 15:00.300
with the imagination of the ceramicist.

15:01.280 --> 15:02.280
What techniques?

15:03.560 --> 15:05.620
Like ceramic stapling and kintsugi.

15:05.840 --> 15:07.680
Ceramic stapling can be applied to some

15:07.680 --> 15:09.210
more complex vessel shapes

15:09.480 --> 15:11.010
to make the works stronger.

15:11.440 --> 15:13.600
Kintsugi can focus on artistry

15:14.240 --> 15:16.040
and create more possibilities.

15:16.520 --> 15:18.780
I know a little about what you're saying.

15:20.400 --> 15:21.800
Was what you were just doing

15:21.800 --> 15:23.600
ceramic stapling restoration?

15:24.360 --> 15:24.680
Yes.

15:25.000 --> 15:26.000
As for kintsugi

15:26.200 --> 15:28.320
or other cultural relics restoration techniques,

15:28.320 --> 15:29.450
do you know them all?

15:29.960 --> 15:32.090
I can only say I've done some research.

15:39.600 --> 15:40.130
How is it?

15:40.440 --> 15:42.770
My little pavilion has some style, right?

15:44.600 --> 15:45.200
Recently,

15:45.360 --> 15:46.220
our Jingdezhen

15:46.800 --> 15:48.480
will have a large number of tourists coming.

15:48.480 --> 15:50.680
So let's bring out these pretty and fun,

15:51.240 --> 15:52.960
affordable small plates and bowls

15:52.960 --> 15:53.880
to sell.

15:54.440 --> 15:55.320
You two sit here

15:55.440 --> 15:56.360
and sell well.

15:56.640 --> 15:57.900
Be the face of the shop,

15:58.160 --> 15:58.600
got it?

16:01.600 --> 16:04.000
The girl is pretty, and the guy is handsome.

16:05.520 --> 16:07.980
Alright, I won't stay here and be an eyesore.

16:08.600 --> 16:10.440
Don't just focus on romance, got it?

16:10.440 --> 16:12.640
Get this month's sales performance up.

16:17.280 --> 16:19.200
We used to just visit the market.

16:19.800 --> 16:20.960
I never expected

16:21.360 --> 16:23.420
we'd actually be stall owners today.

16:26.840 --> 16:29.170
How much for these little cups with words?

16:29.280 --> 16:30.280
Thirty yuan each.

16:30.320 --> 16:32.520
Do you have the words 'Zhuge' and 'Ran'?

16:33.200 --> 16:34.600
I can't seem to find them.

16:36.240 --> 16:37.240
Found them. Here.

16:38.960 --> 16:39.960
Please wrap them up for me.

16:39.960 --> 16:40.800
Okay, thanks.

16:40.840 --> 16:41.370
Found it.

16:42.600 --> 16:43.260
Here you go.

16:43.960 --> 16:45.020
You can scan there.

16:45.200 --> 16:46.600
It's sixty yuan in total.

16:46.720 --> 16:47.320
Thank you.

16:47.360 --> 16:48.490
Alright, take care.

16:48.520 --> 16:49.120
How was it?

16:49.560 --> 16:51.220
Doesn't seem too hard, right?

16:51.360 --> 16:52.760
It's quite interesting.

16:53.600 --> 16:54.280
How about

16:55.080 --> 16:56.940
you try it with the next customer?

16:59.400 --> 17:01.600
I'm right here beside you, don't worry.

17:06.640 --> 17:07.170
You do it.

17:08.720 --> 17:10.119
Feel free to look around.

17:18.160 --> 17:20.160
Are you deciding between these two?

17:20.880 --> 17:21.810
How did you know?

17:23.359 --> 17:25.290
For these small animal ornaments,

17:25.480 --> 17:27.040
it's buy one, get one free.

17:27.280 --> 17:28.920
If you like them both,

17:29.040 --> 17:30.000
you can take them together.

17:30.000 --> 17:30.720
Thirty yuan.

17:30.720 --> 17:31.560
I'll take both then.

17:31.560 --> 17:32.720
Please wrap them up.

17:33.160 --> 17:33.720
Okay.

17:34.080 --> 17:34.610
Alright.

17:35.640 --> 17:36.000
Here.

17:37.360 --> 17:37.840
Take care.

17:37.840 --> 17:38.440
Take care.

17:40.360 --> 17:40.960
Relax.

17:42.080 --> 17:42.880
You did great.

17:45.280 --> 17:46.400
I'm just like this.

17:46.840 --> 17:48.560
Every time I see strangers,

17:48.640 --> 17:49.840
I easily get nervous.

17:50.240 --> 17:51.500
But when you talk to me,

17:51.720 --> 17:52.650
aren't you fine?

17:54.240 --> 17:55.770
Because we know each other.

18:27.440 --> 18:27.920
You see,

18:28.120 --> 18:28.800
I told you.

18:28.840 --> 18:30.840
We still need to do mid-to-high end.

18:31.400 --> 18:32.520
At this rate,

18:32.920 --> 18:34.720
our trip to Taoxichuan

18:35.480 --> 18:37.560
and selling the studio stuff

18:37.720 --> 18:39.320
didn't even cover the travel

18:39.400 --> 18:40.460
and food expenses.

18:42.160 --> 18:44.400
Once we run the studio and the exhibition

18:44.400 --> 18:45.400
properly,

18:45.920 --> 18:46.920
and get investment,

18:46.920 --> 18:48.800
I'll open a gallery like this for you

18:48.800 --> 18:50.600
and make you the chief ceramist.

18:51.720 --> 18:52.250
Let's go.

18:53.080 --> 18:53.520
Jing,

18:54.040 --> 18:56.100
I need to discuss something with you.

18:56.720 --> 18:58.520
I want to delay

18:59.200 --> 19:00.480
the exhibition opening a bit.

19:00.480 --> 19:01.760
And we need more hands.

19:02.200 --> 19:03.040
Do you have

19:03.400 --> 19:04.330
any candidates?

19:10.160 --> 19:12.020
Just take your time polishing it.

19:16.120 --> 19:17.580
Sorry to bother you again.

19:20.760 --> 19:23.200
I don't think I introduced myself last time.

19:23.200 --> 19:24.530
My name is Fang Xiaqing.

19:24.680 --> 19:27.010
The pieces you saw in Taoxichuan earlier,

19:27.480 --> 19:29.360
and the one I showed you last time,

19:30.600 --> 19:31.660
were all made by me.

19:34.160 --> 19:35.520
So you are here to...

19:35.760 --> 19:36.360
I

19:36.800 --> 19:38.060
am here to recruit you.

19:38.400 --> 19:40.200
I hope you can join my studio.

19:44.560 --> 19:45.320
Sorry,

19:45.320 --> 19:46.920
I might be a bit abrupt today.

19:47.280 --> 19:49.360
I wonder if you have time

19:49.360 --> 19:50.960
to visit my studio.

19:51.440 --> 19:53.840
My partner might explain it in more detail.

20:01.280 --> 20:01.880
This is it.

20:02.200 --> 20:02.860
We're here.

20:02.920 --> 20:03.480
Come in.

20:06.240 --> 20:08.400
These two rooms are our studio.

20:08.720 --> 20:09.850
This is the tearoom,

20:10.000 --> 20:11.860
and inside is the main workspace.

20:19.960 --> 20:21.400
This is our studio,

20:21.840 --> 20:23.440
and it's also where we live.

20:24.280 --> 20:25.140
Come, this way.

20:30.360 --> 20:31.920
This is Tian Yuan, and this is Xiaoyu.

20:31.920 --> 20:32.320
Hello.

20:32.320 --> 20:33.440
They are our roommates,

20:33.440 --> 20:35.240
and also our partners in the studio.

20:35.240 --> 20:35.800
Hello.

20:35.800 --> 20:36.400
Hello.

20:36.560 --> 20:37.220
We are busy.

20:37.560 --> 20:39.000
Just pretend we've stood up

20:39.000 --> 20:39.860
and hugged you.

20:40.920 --> 20:41.480
Welcome.

20:41.640 --> 20:42.480
We'll leave you to it.

20:42.480 --> 20:42.840
Okay.

20:43.440 --> 20:44.560
If you want it,

20:44.560 --> 20:46.440
you can note down the item number.

20:47.280 --> 20:47.880
Then,

20:47.880 --> 20:49.360
you can contact me privately.

20:49.360 --> 20:50.440
That's all for

20:50.480 --> 20:51.520
today's livestream.

20:51.520 --> 20:52.120
Bye-bye.

20:52.760 --> 20:55.020
You're ending the stream just like that?

20:56.040 --> 20:57.280
I streamed for an hour

20:57.400 --> 20:58.730
with only five viewers.

21:00.920 --> 21:02.120
Let me introduce you.

21:02.120 --> 21:03.080
This is Jingjing,

21:03.080 --> 21:04.140
the boss of Banlan.

21:05.760 --> 21:06.820
You've met before.

21:06.920 --> 21:07.760
You are

21:07.880 --> 21:08.800
Xu Xiao.

21:09.240 --> 21:11.500
You're the one from Taoxichuan that day.

21:11.640 --> 21:12.640
Yes, exactly.

21:13.640 --> 21:14.570
Here for a visit?

21:14.640 --> 21:15.080
Yes.

21:15.160 --> 21:16.490
Okay, look around then.

21:17.280 --> 21:17.680
Come.

21:18.840 --> 21:20.760
These are our works at Banlan.

21:21.240 --> 21:22.720
Look at these flowers.

21:23.120 --> 21:25.850
They are discarded items I collected from a kiln.

21:26.240 --> 21:29.240
I used broken porcelain of different colors and textures

21:29.240 --> 21:30.570
to piece them together.

21:32.680 --> 21:34.720
Are the basic materials for all your works

21:34.720 --> 21:36.380
discarded porcelain pieces?

21:36.640 --> 21:37.040
Yes.

21:39.520 --> 21:40.760
Why did you think of

21:40.760 --> 21:42.440
using these discarded porcelain pieces?

21:42.440 --> 21:43.570
Because it's cheap.

21:44.240 --> 21:44.680
True.

21:46.000 --> 21:46.440
So,

21:46.560 --> 21:47.840
after seeing these works,

21:47.840 --> 21:48.770
do you like them?

21:50.240 --> 21:51.440
They are very unique.

21:57.120 --> 21:57.560
Here.

21:58.760 --> 21:59.600
Thank you.

22:00.920 --> 22:02.520
You haven't answered me yet.

22:02.640 --> 22:04.100
Do you want to work with me?

22:10.160 --> 22:10.800
It's okay.

22:11.160 --> 22:12.020
Take your time.

22:12.120 --> 22:13.520
Contact me when you've decided.

22:13.520 --> 22:13.880
Okay.

22:24.320 --> 22:26.000
So what do you think?

22:28.280 --> 22:29.720
This Fang Xiaqing...

22:31.080 --> 22:31.760
She...

22:32.600 --> 22:33.460
What about her?

22:33.760 --> 22:35.020
I criticized her work.

22:35.640 --> 22:37.100
Not only was she not angry,

22:37.400 --> 22:39.600
but she also invited me to collaborate.

22:39.840 --> 22:41.970
Instead of being a sculpture teacher,

22:42.680 --> 22:45.410
she came to Jingdezhen to do cultural creations.

22:46.520 --> 22:48.320
Actually, I also want to explore

22:49.040 --> 22:50.240
whether cultural relic restoration can be

22:50.240 --> 22:51.770
combined with ceramic art.

22:52.880 --> 22:53.480
Maybe.

22:58.560 --> 22:59.360
What's wrong?

23:04.160 --> 23:05.120
Nothing.

23:14.480 --> 23:15.040
I

23:15.520 --> 23:17.400
think Fang Xiaqing's studio is pretty good.
